  • Constructor Details

    • Command

      public Command(@NotNull @NotNull ImprovedPlugin plugin, @NotNull @NotNull String name)
      Constructor for a command. Default messages will be loaded from config file.

      The config file must be named "config.yml" and must be located in the plugin folder. The default messages are:

      • noPermissionMessage: You don't have the permission to execute this command.
      • noConsoleMessage: This command can only be executed by a player.
      If you want to change the default messages, you can do this by adding the following lines to your config file: 
         messages:
     noPermissionMessage: You don't have the permission to execute this command.
     noConsoleMessage: This command can only be executed by a player.
      Parameters:
      plugin - plugin which is using this command
      name - name of the command

      public final void executeCommand(@NotNull @NotNull net.md_5.bungee.api.CommandSender sender, @NotNull @NotNull String[] args, @NotNull @NotNull String commandName)
      Executes all annotated command handling methods with the given command name. Throws a RuntimeException if no method was found. Throws a RuntimeException if the return type of one method is not boolean.
      Parameters:
      sender - The sender of the command
      args - String[] of arguments
      commandName - name of the subcommand which should be executed

    • onTabComplete

      public Iterable<String> onTabComplete(@NotNull @NotNull net.md_5.bungee.api.CommandSender sender, @NotNull @NotNull String[] args, @NotNull @NotNull Iterable<String> prefilled)
      This method is called after the framework has already done some prefilling of the tab complete. It will receive a prefilled set of strings which can be modified and finally returned to the player.
      Parameters:
      sender - the sender of the command
      args - the arguments of the command
      prefilled - the prefilled set of strings
      Returns:
      the final set of strings which will be sent to the player
